Collection.Name: Non-HDL Cholesterol Calculation
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
To calculate Total CHOLESTEROL: HDL + LDL +TG/5

                   DESIRABLE          BORDERLINE RISK          HIGH RISK
CHOLESTEROL        <200 mg/dL          200-240 mg/dL           >240 mg/dL

HDL-CHOLESTEROL     >55 mg/dL            25-55 mg/dL            <25 mg/dL

LDL-CHOLESTEROL    <130 mg/dL          130-160 mg/dL           >160 mg/dL

LDL/HDL            2.7 = Optimal   (1/2 average risk)
                   4.0 = Average   (1 X average risk)
                   7.0 = Moderate  (2 X average risk)
                  10.0 = High      (3 X average risk)

       "RISK" = The risk of progressive Coronary Artery Disease"
